  "B8-3": (
    caption: [Box 8-3 Figure. Some growth rings in this wood are much wider than others. The innermost ring marked “Good year” is very wide, with abundant early wood (the lighter, inner part) as well as late wood (the darker, outer part). Conditions must have been very good for the tree that year: It might have been a summer of optimal temperatures or rain; if a cultivated tree, it might have been fertilized that year; or surrounding trees that had been shading it either might have died or been cut away. The next two growth rings, both marked “Poor year,” were produced when the tree was not vigorous enough to make very much wood.],
    path: "../fig/fig-2025-12-12-11-47-48.png"
